caption: First time here but won't be the last! Mushroom truffle ravioli from restaurant week menu were amazing! Generously stuffed with mushrooms and you could really taste the truffle. The salmon dish I ordered on the regular menu was another winner, cooked to perfection with lots of spinach and mushroom and a very flavorful sauce. Small restaurant with upscale yet relaxing ambience and attentive service too.

Came here for dinner and to see if we'd want to have our rehearsal dinner here. Great food and service, and an amazing downstairs event room! Very affordable for being in the most expensive part of Chicago.

The food was delicious and came out promptly. Joe, the manager, checked in on us and made sure we had a wonderful evening. HIGHLY RECOMMEND! We are also having our wedding reception here next fall and we couldn’t be happier with our venue choice after a night of incredible service and food. Francescas makes you feel like you’re part of the family.

The worst and most insulting part of it all was they added more to the bill —stuff we didn’t even order and then didn’t even give a discount for a party of 9 with the insane amount of mistakes they made . My Fiancé went to Francesca’s on Chestnut last night to celebrate our 9 year anniversary! When we arrived at Francesca it was super busy and waited a bit to be seated. When we were seated, it wasn’t the best seat in the house. We sat at the back right wall where the neighbors next to you were only a foot away. It was very cramped and you couldn’t even hear yourself think. We sat for 10 min with no waiter in sight. My fiancé and I were a little annoyed so we made the tough decision to leave. We went to the front and he explained to the hostess what was going on. She was so sweet and begged us not to go. She even complimented my hair and makeup! She immediately gave us one of the best seats in the house by the window! The manager came and apologized for our 1st experience and gave us a celebratory glass of champagne! We also had the lead waiter for the evening who was excellent! They definitely turned our experience around for the better! The food was amazing and so was the service! I am so grateful to the hostess (with the blond hair), the manager, and head waiter for an amazing dinner! They definitely made us feel special!

Francesca's on Chestnut is part of a family of Trattorias across town that serve a solid, dependable and satisfying Italian menu. This particular location benefits from the lack of other reasonable Italians in the area and, I dare say it may well be the only reasonably priced restaurant of any cuisine in the area. It can get busy in there and not all the staff can take the bustle with the same equanimity than some. Still, the overall experience is consistently one of friendliness, of deft tastes and of rich aromas.
